HEADWORD: Mercaptide
<hw>Mer*cap"tide</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A compound of mercaptan formed by replacing its
sulphur hydrogen by a metal; <as>as, potassium <ex>mercaptide</ex>,
<chform>C2H5SK</chform></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

